[{"id":"VR816480","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows the graph of a curve labeled P equals the fraction a over V in a gridded plane. The horizontal axis is labeled “Volume.” The vertical axis is labeled “Pressure.” There are horizontal and vertical gridlines drawn at equal distance, respectively, in the plane. The curve begins at the point that is one gridline to the right of the vertical axis and 5 gridlines above the horizontal axis, moves downward and to the right, steeply at first and then more gradually, and ends at the point that is 5 gridlines to the right of the vertical axis and one gridline above the horizontal axis.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR816480.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A sample of an ideal gas is in a sealed container with a moveable piston. During a thermodynamic process, the pressure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\"><math alttext=\"P\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>P</mi></math></span></span> and volume <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"V\"><math alttext=\"V\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>V</mi></math></span></span> of the gas can be described by the equation <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P equals the fraction a over V\"><math alttext=\"P equals the fraction a over V\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>a</mi><mi>V</mi></mfrac></math></span></span>, where <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"a\"><math alttext=\"a\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>a</mi></math></span></span> is a positive constant with appropriate units. The graph shows <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\"><math alttext=\"P\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>P</mi></math></span></span> as a function of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"V\"><math alttext=\"V\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>V</mi></math></span></span> during the process. Which of the following claims best describes how the temperature of the gas changes, if at all, during the process?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR816480_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The temperature decreases.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The temperature increases.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The temperature remains constant.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The temperature could decrease, increase, or stay the same depending on how many atoms are in the gas.</p>"],"answer":2}]